>https://pastebin.com/4NQgF4Xp

Promised I'd be waiting for it. I like it. First bit sets it up pretty nicely and the second part is pretty damn good. On criticism, I can't say much regarding it being a short amount and all, though one bit is that you can replace the periods at the end of dialogue with commas and lower case the word that follows right after. Like this:

>"Good morning... A-Anon," she greets back, not meeting your gaze.
>"I'm okay. Just tired," she responds weakly before taking a sip of her juice.

Another tip is that ellipsis at the end of dialogue like this work as four dots than three and the quotation mark or a comma.

>"I'm sorry...." she whimpers.

But either way, it's pretty minor stuff. If you're up for it, I do want to see more.
